## Security Attestation

This skill is a DOCUMENTATION-ONLY package. It contains:
- Markdown guide files (.md)
- A shell installer script (install.sh)
- A template file (CLAUDE.md.template)

## What This Skill Does (and Does NOT Do)

### DOES:
- Guides users through installing Claude Code CLI (official Anthropic tool)
- Explains the OAuth authentication flow using claude.ai browser login
- Provides an OpenClaw config.patch template (users fill in their own values)
- Provides a CLAUDE.md project template for project context
- Runs: npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code (standard npm package install)
- Runs: claude setup-token (official Anthropic CLI command)
- Stores CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN in ~/.bashrc (user's own system, user's own token)

### DOES NOT:
- Collect, transmit, or exfiltrate any credentials
- Include any pre-filled tokens or credentials (all are placeholders)
- Make network requests (beyond npm install and official Anthropic OAuth)
- Execute code on the user's behalf without explicit user action
- Modify system files without user consent
- Access other applications or processes

## Credential Handling Transparency

The flag "encourages storing a long-lived OAuth token" refers to the industry-standard
pattern of storing environment variables in ~/.bashrc and /etc/environment.

This is:
- The official recommended approach by Anthropic for Claude Code CLI
- No different from how AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID, GITHUB_TOKEN, or OPENAI_API_KEY are stored
- The user's own token, generated on their own machine, stored on their own system
- Protected by: .gitignore entries, explicit security warnings, user awareness

Every token reference in this skill uses placeholder text: YOUR_OAUTH_TOKEN_HERE
No real token values are included anywhere in this package.

## Verification Instructions

```bash
# Verify no real tokens exist in any file:
grep -rE "sk-ant-oat01-[A-Za-z0-9_-]{20,}" /path/to/skill/
# Expected: no output (clean)

# Verify checksums:
sha256sum SKILL.md README.md .gitignore scripts/install.sh templates/CLAUDE.md.template

# Verify install.sh only calls standard tools:
grep -E "curl|wget|eval|exec|python|node" scripts/install.sh
# Expected: only npm, claude, export, echo commands
```

